<dl id="n05033f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05033f">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05033f"> 33(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tonsure unknown in W / earthstains</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Saint&apos;s face was pinched and worn with fastings, watchings, and other austerities. His clothes were poor and blotched with <mark>earth-stains</mark> from his prostrations. <mark>His hair was close shaven, after the fashion of the monk of the East, as yet unfamiliar to Western Christianity</mark>. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 40</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
